1.6 Create A New Incident
Lesson
An incident is a record of an unplanned interruption or degradation of service that needs to be resolved to restore normal operations. Incidents are the foundation of IT Service Management (ITSM) in ServiceNow.

When creating incidents, be specific in descriptions: "Cannot print to 3rd floor color printer" is better than "printer broken". Keep the incident current with work notes as you investigate the submitted record. Many organizations create incident templates for common issues to speed up logging. When closing, always include what fixed the issue in the Resolution Notes field.

Scenario
You are Beth Anglin, an ITIL agent working the service desk. Fred Luddy has just called reporting that his Conference Event Mobile App for Staff won't launch and is showing error 555. The conference starts in 3 hours, making this urgent. Your task is to create and document this incident properly in ServiceNow.

Task Objectives

1. Impersonate Beth Anglin to log the incident.

2. Create a complete incident record with the following filled in:

- Caller: Fred Luddy
- Category: Software
- Subcategory: None
- Short Description: Cannot get the Conference Event Mobile app for staff to launch. It is flashing error 555.
- Description: It was working yesterday, but not this morning. This is urgent! The event starts in 3 hours.
- Service: Conference Event Services
- Service Offering: Event Mobile for Staff Service Offering
- Configuration item: Event Mobile for Staff Application
- Channel: Phone
- State: (Leave as New)
- Impact: 1-High
- Urgency: 1-High
- Priority: (Automatically calculated as 1-Critical)
- Assignment group: (Leave blank)
- Assigned to: (Leave blank)


3. Document both internal work notes and customer-facing comments.

- Work notes: No outages have been reported, am routing to the Conference Event App support team.
- Additional comments: Fred, we are working on getting the app up and running.

4. Ensure proper service mapping and assignment routing.

1.7 Receive The Work Assignments 
Lesson
Favorites in ServiceNow allow you to bookmark frequently accessed pages, forms, lists, reports, or dashboards for quick access. They appear as a dedicated menu in your navigation, eliminating the need to repeatedly search through the Application Navigator.

Example use cases – Service Desk Agent:
- My Open Incidents
- Unassigned Queue
- Incident Dashboard
- Knowledge Base Search
Scenario
You are a ServiceNow agent who frequently needs to access the My Groups Work module to review unassigned work items for your team. To improve your workflow efficiency, you need to add this module to your Favorites for quick access. Your task is to add the My Groups Work module as a favorite, and verify it appears in your Favorites menu.

Task Objectives
1. Navigate to the Service Desk application in the All menu.

2. Add the My Groups Work module to your Favorites.

3. Access the module through the Favorites menu.

1.8 Explore the Service Operations WorkSpace
Lesson
The Service Operations Workspace provides a unified interface for managing IT Service Management (ITSM) workflows. It enables IT agents to handle the lifecycle of task records—such as incidents, requests, and walk-ups—through a modern, streamlined interface. In this simulator task, you will take on the role of an IT agent and work an incident from assignment through resolution using the Service Operations Workspace.

Scenario
You are Beth Anglin, an IT support agent. A critical incident has been reported by Fred Luddy regarding an error with the Mobile Event App. Your task is to locate the unassigned critical incident in the Service Operations Workspace, assign it to yourself, use Agent Assist to find a relevant knowledge article, share the article with the caller, and resolve the incident with appropriate resolution notes.

Task Objectives

This task requires you to impersonate another user. You must end the impersonation before selecting Show hint or Validate task.

1. Impersonate Beth Anglin.

2. Navigate the Service Operations Workspace as Beth, and locate unassigned critical incidents.

3. Accept incident assignment and take ownership of the record.

4. Leverage Agent Assist to find and attach relevant knowledge articles to incidents:
- Select the graduation cap icon in the right-side panel of the Service Operations Workspace to open Agent Assist.
- Locate and attach the article: Mobile Event App for Staff – Error 555

5. Resolve incidents with appropriate resolution codes and notes
- Resolution code: Workaround provided
- Resolution notes: Used vendor instructions to restart client.
1.9 Explore the Employee Center
Lesson
The Employee Center serves as a centralized portal for addressing internal employee needs across departments such as HR, IT, and Legal. As a default ServiceNow Store application, it provides employees with a one-stop-shop to access services, submit requests, track incidents, and find helpful resources. In this simulation, you'll navigate the Employee Center from an employee's perspective to understand how end-users interact with the platform and resolve their issues.

Scenario
You are a ServiceNow administrator learning how to support end-users who interact with the Employee Center Portal. To better understand the employee experience, you need to impersonate an employee user and navigate through the portal to see how they access services, view their requests, and find resolution information for their incidents.
Fred Luddy, one of your organization's employees, recently reported an issue with the Conference Event Mobile app and received a resolution. Your task is to impersonate Fred, navigate to the Employee Center, review his submitted requests, and verify that he can access the knowledge base article that helped resolve his incident.

Task Objectives

This task requires you to impersonate another user. You must end the impersonation before selecting Show hint or Validate task.

1. Impersonate Fred Luddy.

2. Navigate to and explore the Employee Center Portal interface.

3. Locate and review submitted requests and incidents.

4. Access the incident Fred reported regarding the Conference Event Mobile app.

5. Mark the associated article as helpful.

6. Properly end the impersonation session.

To begin, navigate to the User menu > Impersonate user.
